    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWith the release of 0.12, we have now a built-in plugins API(install, update, uninstall ...) but unlike the lsp file-system introduced with 0.11, we need to go for configurations option, using the `vim.pack.{action}` API\n```lua\n-- init.lua\n\n-- first installing the plugin\nvim.pack.add({\n  'https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter',\n  -- more plugins here\n})\n\n-- then we will add the config options, setup/customize it:\nrequire('nvim-treesitter').setup {\n  -- Directory to install parsers and queries to (prepended to `runtimepath` to have priority)\n  install_dir = vim.fn.stdpath('data') .. '/site'\n}\n```\n\nWith lsp for example, all we would need is to create a file inside the `lsp` directory with the same name, e.g. `~/.config/nvim/lsp/lua_ls.lua` or `~/.config/nvim/lsp/vtsls.lua`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIMO, a **conventions over configurations** plugins file-system would be better since we were already using that before 0.12 with **lazy.nvim** plugin manager, the migration would be easier if we would have the same file-system, a **plugins** folder inside `~/.config/nvim`, with the same plugin author+name, e.g.:\n```\n|-- ~/.config/nvim/\n    |-- plugins/\n        |-- nvim-treesitter@nvim-treesitter.lua\n        |-- folke@tokyonight.nvim.lua\n        |-- saghen@blink.cmp.lua\n```\nNow all we would need to do is to put the config options inside that lua plugin file, e.g.:\n```lua\n-- ~/.config/nvim/plugins/nvim-treesitter@nvim-treesitter.lua\nrequire('nvim-treesitter').setup {\n  -- Directory to install parsers and queries to (prepended to `runtimepath` to have priority)\n  install_dir = vim.fn.stdpath('data') .. '/site'\n}\n```\n\nNo need to do the install step manually via `vim.pack.add(GITHUB_PATH)`, or to require the `~/.config/nvim/plugins/nvim-treesitter@nvim-treesitter.lua` file.\nEasy, clean !\n\nThe file convention here is `{AUTHOR}@{REPO}.lua`, or we could go for a directory config instead:\n```\n|-- ~/.config/nvim/\n    |-- plugins/\n        |-- nvim-treesitter/\n           |-- nvim-treesitter.lua\n        |-- folke/\n           |-- tokyonight.nvim.lua\n           |-- trouble.nvim.lua\n        |-- saghen/\n           |-- blink.cmp.lua\n```\nOf course we will keep the current config plugin system, but we will fetch for the file convention first, conventions then configurations :)",
