            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "**Before**(current):\n1. add `vim.pack.add` to your `init.lua` file\n```lua\n-- init.lua\nvim.pack.add({'https://github.com/nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter'})\n```\n2. add a `require` inside your `init.lua` file for the custom plugin config\n```lua\n-- init.lua\nrequire(\"plugins.nvim-treesitter\")\n```\n3. create the custom plugin lua file\n```lua\n-- lua/plugins/nvim-treesitter.lua\nrequire('nvim-treesitter').setup {\n  -- Directory to install parsers and queries to (prepended to `runtimepath` to have priority)\n  install_dir = vim.fn.stdpath('data') .. '/site'\n}\n```\n\n**After**(with the COC plugins file-system):\n1. just create the plugin file with the convention naming inside the plugins folder, easy, clean :\n```lua\n-- plugins/nvim-treesitter@nvim-treesitter.lua\nrequire('nvim-treesitter').setup {\n  -- Directory to install parsers and queries to (prepended to `runtimepath` to have priority)\n  install_dir = vim.fn.stdpath('data') .. '/site'\n}\n```",
