            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> > what problem is this solving?\n> \n> [@justinmk](https://github.com/justinmk) no need for calling `vim.pack.add`, just creating a lua file inside the plugins folder, no need to `require` that lua config file too inside `init.lua`,\n\nthere already is no need to `require()` a plugin unless the plugin is badly designed. see `:help lua-plugin-init`. the plugin should automatically initialize itself via its own `plugin/foo.lua` file.\n\nalso as clason mentioned, users can create their own `plugin/*.lua` files which already automatically run at startup.\n",
